{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8fab40f6-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2384"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2384"},"text":"§ 2384.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Statutory officers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8fab40f7-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2384/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appointment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The President may appoint, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, twelve officers in the agency primarily responsible for administering subchapter I of this chapter, and in the selection of one of such persons due consideration shall be given to persons qualified as professional engineers.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8fab40f8-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2384/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rate of compensation; title of officers; order of succession","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Within the limitations established by subsection (a) of this section, the President may fix the rate of compensation, and may designate the title of, any officer appointed pursuant to the authority contained in that subsection. The President may also fix the order of succession among the officers provided for in subsection (a) of this section in the event of the absence, death, resignation, or disability of one or more of said officers.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8fab40f9-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2384/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appointment of certain statutory officers to comparable positions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any person who was appointed by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, to any statutory position authorized by any provision of law repealed by section 642(a) and who is serving in one of such positions at the time of transfer of functions pursuant to subsections (c) and (d) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2381"},"text":"section 2381 of this title","children":[],"tail":", may be appointed by the President to a comparable position authorized by subsection (a) of this section on the date of the establishment of the agency primarily responsible for administering subchapter I of this chapter, without further action by the Senate."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8fab40fa-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2384/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/88/tI/s124/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–88, title I, § 124(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-03"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/541"},"text":"91 Stat. 541","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8fab40fb-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2384/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Coordinator for security assistance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In addition to the officers otherwise provided for in this section, the President shall appoint, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, one officer for the purpose of coordinating security assistance programs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8fab40fc-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 624, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-04"},"text":"Sept. 4, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/447"},"text":"75 Stat. 447","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/565"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–565","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 302(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/262"},"text":"76 Stat. 262","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/205"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–205","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 302(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/388"},"text":"77 Stat. 388","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/tIII/s305/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426, title III, § 305(33)","children":[],"tail":", (42), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-14"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/426"},"text":"78 Stat. 426","children":[],"tail":", 428; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/171"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–171","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 302(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/660"},"text":"79 Stat. 660","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/583"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–583","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 302(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-19"},"text":"Sept. 19, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/807"},"text":"80 Stat. 807","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/137"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–137","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 302(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/460"},"text":"81 Stat. 460","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/175"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–175","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 304, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1969","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/821"},"text":"83 Stat. 821","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/226"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–226","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 302, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-02-07"},"text":"Feb. 7, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/28"},"text":"86 Stat. 28","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/329/tIII/s301/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–329, title III, § 301(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/750"},"text":"90 Stat. 750","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/88/tI/s124/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–88, title I, § 124(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-03"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/541"},"text":"91 Stat. 541","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/105/tI/s109/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–105, title I, § 109(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-17"},"text":"Aug. 17, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/846"},"text":"91 Stat. 846","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/424/tV/s504"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–424, title V, § 504","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/959"},"text":"92 Stat. 959","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/533/tVII/s706"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–533, title VII, § 706","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/3158"},"text":"94 Stat. 3158","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/tVII/s705/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, title VII, § 705(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1545"},"text":"95 Stat. 1545","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/164/tX/s1002/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–164, title X, § 1002(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-11-22"},"text":"Nov. 22, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/1052"},"text":"97 Stat. 1052","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/tI/s162/e/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, title I, § 162(e)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/405"},"text":"108 Stat. 405","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8fab40fd-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8fab40fe-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id8fab40ff-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 642(a), referred to in subsec. (c), means ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195/s642/a"},"text":"section 642(a) of Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", which is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2151"},"text":"section 2151 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id8fab4100-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (f) which provided for an Assistant Secretary of State for Human Rights and Humanitarian Affairs and prescribed the Assistant Secretary’s duties."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—Subsec. (f)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/164"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–164","children":[],"tail":" inserted provisions relating to providing advice to the Administrator of the Agency for International Development on policy framework."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (g) which related to the Inspector General and the duties, responsibilities, and compensation of such official. See sections 2, 8A, and 11 of the Inspector General Act of 1978, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1101"},"text":"92 Stat. 1101","children":[],"tail":", as amended, set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/533"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–533","children":[],"tail":" substituted in pars. (1) to (5) “Inspector General” for “Auditor General” wherever appearing; in par. (3), imposed upon the Inspector General requirement of supervising, directing, and controlling security activities, including audit, investigative, and security activities relating to programs and operations within the United States International Development Cooperation Agency; in par. (4) required submission of an annual report to the Director; and added pars. (6) to (9)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/424"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–424","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (g)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1977—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/88"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–88","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (d) which provided for an Inspector General, Foreign Assistance."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/105/s109/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–105, § 109(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted references to the Assistant Secretary of State for Human Rights and Humanitarian Affairs for references to the Coordinator for Human Rights and Humanitarian Affairs."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/105/s109/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–105, § 109(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Assistant Secretary of State” for “Coordinator”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1976—Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/329"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–329","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1972—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/226"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–226","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1969—Subsec. (d)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/175/s304/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–175, § 304(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted provision including the Overseas Private Investment Corporation in Inspector General’s reviews and audits, and inserted provision authorizing the conduct of such reviews and audits for programs under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s290f"},"text":"section 290f of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(5), (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/175/s304/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–175, § 304(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), included "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s290f"},"text":"section 290f of this title","children":[],"tail":" within provisions of this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1967—Subsec. (d)(2)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/137"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–137","children":[],"tail":" struck out “of assistance” after “programs” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1966—Subsec. (d)(8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/583"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–583","children":[],"tail":" added par. (8)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1965—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/171/s302/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–171, § 302(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “paragraph (3) of” before “subsection (a) of this section” the second time it appears and substituted “of one or more of said officers” for “of the officers provided for in paragraphs (1) and (2) of that subsection”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(2)(A), (5), (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/171/s302/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–171, § 302(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the Latin American Development Act, as amended” for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/735"},"text":"Public Law 86–735","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1964—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/s305/42"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426, § 305(42)","children":[],"tail":", repealed provisions which related to the appointment of an Under Secretary, Deputy Under Secretary and ten Assistant Secretaries and prescribed their rates of compensation."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/426/s305/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–426, § 305(33)","children":[],"tail":", repealed provisions which prescribed the compensation of the Inspector General, Deputy Inspector General and Assistant Inspector Generals. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5315"},"text":"section 5315 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1963—Subsec. (a)(2), (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/205/s302/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–205, § 302(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), reduced the number of Deputy Under Secretaries from two to one in par. (2), and increased the number of Assistant Secretaries from 9 to 10 in par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/205/s302/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–205, § 302(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", made conforming changes in language to reflect that only one Deputy Under Secretary may now be appointed."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/205/s302/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–205, § 302(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “who shall be appointed by the President by and with the advice and consent of the Senate,” and increased the salary of the Deputy Inspector General, Foreign Assistance, from $19,500 to $20,000."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1962—Subsecs. (d), (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/565"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–565","children":[],"tail":" redesignated subsec. (e) as (d), inserted “, and programs being conducted by United States Government Agencies under sections 1942 to 1945 of this title,” in par. 2(A), and “, and sections 1942 to 1945 of this title,” in pars. (5) and (7), and repealed former subsec. (d) which related to the temporary continuation of certain statutory positions."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id8fab4101-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8fab4102-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References to Subchapter I Deemed To Include Certain Parts of Subchapter II","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"References to subchapter I of this chapter are deemed to include parts IV (§ 2346 et seq.), VI (§ 2348 et seq.), and VIII (§ 2349aa et seq.